n=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#993300>(5/27/03 10:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Settling in for the day</span><hr size=1> She was tired. Though trekking through mountains was one of the things that she did best, she too was human, and could not go forever without sleeping. Though she was a light sleeper, as people like her had to be, she did enjoy to sleep on the rare occasion.<br>
The amazon moved under some shelter. The weather was no optimal to be travelling, and the last thing that she desired was to be rained on in the middle of the night. If any amazons showed up soon, she would know about it, but for the time being, she would stay put and watch the former village, making sure that no one saw fit to come through and perhaps take their bit of amazon relics.<br>
Kalasin laid down on the ground, pulling some hay over the top of her, which she knew from experience would keep her warn, and at the same time make her barely visible to anyone passing through. She laid on her stomach and pulled out a piece of scroll that she had in her pack, along with that she pulled out a quill and some ink, and in a mixture of languages, she started to write. The young woman was not a master of any particular language, and her script was often a mixture of Latin, Arabic, the language of the Chinese, and those further east, only because her husband was from the furthest land to the east.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>“Caus-Caus… it is an interesting place. Nothing here though, which is a shame, I would have liked to find someone perhaps. But I am going to stay put for a day or two, see if anyone shows.”<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=celticmorrigan>Celtic Morrigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady of the Lake</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#993300>(5/28/03 7:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/thephantomqueen/images/morrigan26.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Settling in for the day</span><hr size=1> A crow was following close behind as the visitor of the Causcaus trekked through, squacking loudly as she walked. When she stopped, she fly a bit ahead, to where there was deep tree cover. Once there, the crow landed and began to change into its human form. A 6 foot 6 inch woman stood where the crow once landed. Her black as night hair hung to the back of her knees. She wore a black leather halter and skirt, with boots up to her thighs. Across her back was her claymore sword. Her black eyes turned green as she walked to where she saw Kalasin stop, approaching her on silent footfalls. <p><img border=0 src="http://members.aol.com/thephantomqueen/images/button.gif" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#993300>(5/28/03 8:37 pm)<