was the only one that she worshipped, there were a few she respected, and the rest, well, she stayed out of their way, and they stayed out of hers.<br>
&quot;My name is Kalasin Dido Yamamoto Ti'Ya-Kuk'Tai.&quot;<br>
She did not expect the goddess to have heard of her, she had never been to Eire, though Rhiannon, a sister amazon of hers, had come from there, so she knew the accent perfectly well.<br>
&quot;It's good to know that you have confidence in your abilities though.&quot; She smiled and put the dagger away. &quot;As for me, I'm only one to start with the slashing and hacking after someone makes a threat… ask Amaterasu sometime, I am sure she will be glad to tell you all about me.&quot;<br>
Though she did show them some consideration, given that if they so chose, most could wipe her out in a moment, Kalasin refused to treat the gods any different to normal people. As far as she was concerned, if they were people-shaped, they deserved to be treated as such. The only acception was Amaterasu, Kalasin's patron goddess.<br>
She chuckled as the panther moved away.<br>
&quot;Now look, we are boring the feline, can we move onto something else now?&quot;<br>
